post_text:
Google Classroom room instructions:

Here's the process for students to get to google classroom:
- Starting from google.com
- Click on the google apps in the top right corner, which are nine dots in a square
- Find the classroom app
- Students join classrooms by clicking the join button
- After joining, google transitions the student to the classroom screen
- Students have to read what is posted in the classroom for their assignments

post_text:
Snow Day Suggestions:

Our students have several online resources that they can use from home. These resources are used throughout the school day and your child should know their log on information.

K-8 can use MobyMax for all subjects
K-3 can use Razkids for reading practice
Grds 3-8 can use Study Island for all subjects and their individualized learning paths.
Grds 3-8 can use IXL for math practice

Middle School students have specific assignments in Math and Science that they should work on in Khan Academy and Study Island.

And as always, snuggling up and reading together and retelling details of the story is a fun way to stay warm!!

Be safe, stay warm and enjoy!!

JOIN US IN IMPROVING OUR SCHOOL!!

Every year we develop a School Improvement plan that is used to guide our decision making process and instructional practices. We would like our parents and students to take an active role in that decision making. One way to assist is to complete our annual SIP Parent and student surveys. Students will complete their surveys in Library or Computer class over the next few weeks. The parent survey link is available on our website and our facebook page. We hope you will take a few minutes to complete the survey.

The URL link for the parent survey is:

http://www.advanc-ed.org/survey/public/5123578

THANK YOU FOR YOUR CONTINUED SUPPORT AND PARTICIPATION.

post_text:
Last week we were visited by NED's Kindness Adventure. We learned a lot and had a ton of fun! We are currently paying the kindness forward by having a NED's Kindness Adventure sale. We have items made by artisans in Kenya for purchase! Each sale does three things: 1-helps to provide income to Kenyan women who make the items, 2-helps to pay for another school to have the NED Kindness Adventure visit them, free of cost and 3- $0.25 from each purchase goes towards building a well for fresh water for Kenyan communities. Please contribute! The sale will end on Friday, June 8th.

http://www.kindnessadventure.com/giving.html

post_text: As part of the sixth grade trip to Northern Michigan University, we were able to visit Black Rocks which are some of the oldest rock formations on the planet! post_text: We would like to give an extra special shout out to Mrs. Barnwell this week. She has been inducted into The Leona Group Teacher Hall of Fame. She is a force to be reckoned with! She is one of our Girl Scout Troop Leaders. She goes above and beyond to bring fun, educational experiences to our fourth graders and she helps our students love learning. Mrs. Barnwell, you are outstanding! Have an incredible time celebrating all of your hard work at The Leona Group Teacher Hall of Fame luncheon on May 16th. We could not be prouder of you!
